@NODE Outro "EasyElements Hypertext Manual - Outro"

@{u}Outro@{uu}

Now, for some useless blarb!

EasyElements was written on an A1200 with Kickstart/Workbench 3.0, a 250 Meg 2.5" HD, DKB 1240 accelerator with 68EC030/40MHz, 68882/50MHz and 4 Meg of RAM, BSC CD1200 (Tandem1200) with Mitsumi CD-ROM.

EE was written in C and took less than 3 hours to write, including the input of all the elements, the writing of this .guide and the painting of the two icons.

This program is over 2 months old, but I was always too bored to write a doc for it and release it.  Thus the >2 month delay.

Oh yes, I know, the two icons look crap!

@ENDNODE
